SIMPLE: passable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passable
<hw>Pass"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>passable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being passed,
traveled, navigated, traversed, penetrated, or the like; <as>as, the
roads are not <ex>passable</ex>; the stream is <ex>passable</ex>in
boats.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His body's a <qex>passable</qex> carcass if it be not hurt; it is
a throughfare for steel.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being freely circulated or disseminated;
acceptable; generally receivable; current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With men as with false money -- one piece is more or less
<qex>passable</qex> than another.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Could they have made this slander <qex>passable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Collier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Such as may be accepted or allowed to pass without
serious objection; adequate; acceptable; tolerable; admissable;
moderate; mediocre.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>My version will appear a <qex>passable</qex> beauty when the
original muse is absent.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passableness</ent>⟦br⟧
